1) Run programs then reboot
1b) (Do system updates in gnome-software)
2) In tweaks:
	Cursor = Bibata-Modern-Ice
	Icons = Koda or Adwaita (default)
	<>
	<>
	Legacy = Sweet-Dark
	
    In Fonts:
		All to 11 or 12 and scaling to 1.25
	Startup:
		Audacious - alter so it is in systray
	Top Bar: 
		Weekday added
	Window Tabs:
		Max & Min added
3) Extension manager
	In User-Installled add:
		AppIndicator and KStatusNotifierItem Support
		ArcMenu
		Blur my shell
		Burn my windows
		Dash to Dock
		(Dynamic Panel Transparency)
		Just Perfection (Change shell-theme to 'on')
		Mpris Label (Switch in 'Label' 'Hide when paused' to off)
		(Reorder Workspaces) 
		Space bar (Change from Super + W to Super + T and 'show empty workspaces'.  Also turn on shift super + n)
		(Switch workspace (change to ctrl `) )
		Vitals (centre and show Memory in GB)
		Weather o'clock

4) In Settings (right click desktop)
	Click multitasking and change to 4 workspaces
	In Keyboard and View and Customise Shortcuts 
		In Windows add Super+W to close
		In Custom Shortcuts:
			Brave: brave-browser : F9
			Terminal: gnome-terminal : Super + Return
			(logout: /bin/sh -c '~/log.sh' : Super + x)
			pcmanfm: pcmanfm : F12
			geany: geany : Super + g
			(dmenu: dmenu_run -fn "Noto Sans Regular-16" -sb "#990000" -sf "#FFFF66" -p "Run: " : Alt + p)
			Sound : pavucontrol : Super + v
			(System-Monitor: gnome-system-monitor : Super + F3)

 5) In ArcMenu:
		Choose Modern Theme = Plasma
		Font = 11 or 12
		height = 750
